# Onshape Variables

A **Variable Studio** is a document tab (`eid`) that holds named variables shared
across every Part Studio in the document. Each variable has a `name`, a `type`
(`LENGTH` / `ANGLE` / `NUMBER` / `ANY`), and an `expression` string like `"50 mm"`.
A feature parameter elsewhere can reference one with `#myVar` in its own
expression, so variables are the document-wide knobs that drive @onshape/features
and @onshape/partstudios (and they read like the document-scope twin of a
per-element @onshape/configurations input).

## Model

- Addressed by `did/{wv}/{wvid}/e/{eid}` — the middle coordinate is `w`/`v`/`m`
  (workspace / version / microversion). GETs accept any; **writes must target a
  workspace `/w/`**.
- The `eid` is the Variable Studio element. A Part Studio also exposes a *variable
  table*, so the GET returns an **array** — one entry per studio reference visible
  to the element, each carrying a `variableStudioReference` and its `variables[]`.
- Scope is **document-wide**: a variable defined in one studio resolves in any
  Part Studio that references the studio. `variablestudioreferences` lists which
  studios an element pulls in; `variablestudioscope.isAutomaticallyInserted`
  controls whether a new studio is auto-attached to new elements.
- A variable's `value` is the evaluated result of its `expression` (only present
  when the GET is asked for it, via `includeValuesAndReferencedVariables`);
  `expression` is the editable source of truth.

## Endpoints

| METHOD path | purpose |
|---|---|
| `GET …/variables/d/{did}/{wv}/{wvid}/e/{eid}/variables` | contents of all variable tables in an element |
| `GET …/variables/d/{did}/{wv}/{wvid}/e/{eid}/variablestudioreferences` | studio references for an element |
| `GET …/variables/d/{did}/{wv}/{wvid}/e/{eid}/variablestudioscope` | `isAutomaticallyInserted` scope flag |
| `POST …/variables/d/{did}/w/{wid}/e/{eid}/variables` | assign/update variables in a Variable Studio |
| `POST …/variables/d/{did}/w/{wid}/e/{eid}/variablestudioreferences` | set the studio references for an element |
| `POST …/variables/d/{did}/w/{wid}/e/{eid}/variablestudioscope` | set the scope (`isAutomaticallyInserted`) |
| `POST …/variables/d/{did}/w/{wid}/variablestudio` | create a new Variable Studio in a workspace |

GET path coords: `{wv}` is `w`/`v`/`m`, `{wvid}` the matching id. Common queries:
`configuration`, `includeValuesAndReferencedVariables` (GET), `linkDocumentId`
(all). Auth: @onshape/auth.

## Shapes

GET `…/variables` response — array of variable tables, one per referenced studio:

```json
[
  {
    "variableStudioReference": { },
    "variables": [
      {
        "name": "width",
        "type": "LENGTH",
        "expression": "50 mm",
        "value": "0.05",
        "description": ""
      }
    ]
  }
]
```

POST `…/variables` body — a **bare array** of variables to assign to the studio
(send the full set; this replaces the studio's variables):

```json
[
  {
    "name": "width",
    "type": "LENGTH",
    "expression": "50 mm",
    "description": ""
  }
]
```

`type` is one of `LENGTH` / `ANGLE` / `NUMBER` / `ANY`. `ANY`/`NUMBER` take a
unitless `expression` (e.g. `"5"`); `LENGTH`/`ANGLE` take a unit (`"50 mm"`,
`"30 deg"`). `configuredExpression` / `configuredDescription` (`BTConfiguredValue`)
let a value vary per @onshape/configurations. The POST response is `{}`.

## Recipe

Read-only against the kb2 doc. **READ-ONLY** — never POST here; writes go to a
scratch doc you own. Basic auth (`access:secret`) per @onshape/auth, local-testing
only; production signs with HMAC (the runnable signer is
`examples/onshape/onshape_edit.py`, see @onshape/api).

```bash
export ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY=...   # dev-portal.onshape.com
export ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY=...
DID=378e93b0ad360aa043a0220b
WID=09273312fedee7bf3c3482ad
EID=...   # the Variable Studio (or any Part Studio) tab id from the doc URL

# GET every variable table visible to the element, with evaluated values
curl -sfG -u "$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY" \
  -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  --data-urlencode 'includeValuesAndReferencedVariables=true' \
  "https://cad.onshape.com/api/v10/variables/d/$DID/w/$WID/e/$EID/variables" \
  | tee /tmp/onshape_vars.json | python3 -m json.tool
```

Verify — assert a known variable's name + expression, OR accept the empty case
(kb2 may have no Variable Studio; the GET then returns `[]` or tables with empty
`variables[]` — still a valid assertion):

```bash
python3 - <<'PY'
import json
tables = json.load(open('/tmp/onshape_vars.json'))
vars = [v for t in tables for v in t.get('variables', [])]
if not vars:
    print('OK: no variables in this element (empty studio) — []')
else:
    by_name = {v['name']: v for v in vars}
    # adjust to a real name once one exists; example asserts "width" == "50 mm"
    assert 'width' in by_name, f'no "width" var; found {list(by_name)}'
    assert by_name['width']['expression'].replace(' ', '') == '50mm', by_name['width']
    print('OK:', by_name['width']['name'], '=', by_name['width']['expression'])
PY
```

The UI fallback (open the Variable Studio tab, add a row) is @onshape/playwright;
prefer this REST path. To consume a variable, reference `#width` in a feature
`expression` via @onshape/features.
